{
    "id": "electronics/basic-circuit",
    "title": "Build a basic LED circuit",
    "description": "Wire a 5 mm LED and 220 Ω resistor on a breadboard to learn basic circuits.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/electronics_basic_led_breadboard_circuit.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Orion here. Let's light a 5 mm LED with a 220 Ω resistor. Keep the 5 V supply unplugged, remove metal jewelry, and verify the resistor color code before anything touches power.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "Got it. What's in the bench kit?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "Collect a breadboard, two jumper wires, one 5 mm LED, one 220 Ω resistor, a color chart, and a 5 V supply. We only energize after a dry-run inspection confirms polarity and no exposed shorts.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "layout-choice",
                    "text": "Kit assembled and power is still unplugged.",
                    "process": "verify-resistor-color-code",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 2
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "48cf736e-184c-4bd1-b9b0-15b7e9721646",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "037e6065-68a7-4ad1-9b0b-7778ecfe0662",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "bf3d2784-d48d-4b12-b12a-75f563b5dc88",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "828d6c3b-66a5-4064-b221-97630274502b",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "layout-choice",
            "text": "Choose your wiring strategy. Main path: classic series layout. Alternate path: bench preflight, then wire one rail at a time. Either way, we capture an evidence check before finish.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble-main",
                    "text": "Main path: classic series layout"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble-alt",
                    "text": "Alternate path: cautious one-rail-at-a-time"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "assemble-main",
            "text": "Insert the LED with the long leg toward the positive rail. Place the 220 Ω resistor in series to +5 V and return the LED short leg to ground. Keep power unplugged while confirming every connection.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "power-on-check",
                    "text": "Main layout complete and inspected"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "assemble-alt",
            "text": "Build in two passes: first place LED + resistor without power, then route jumpers to rails. Pause after each pass to confirm no lead crosses the opposite rail.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "power-on-check",
                    "text": "Alternate layout complete and inspected"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "power-on-check",
            "text": "Plug in 5 V only after final visual inspection. Evidence gate: LED should glow steadily for a full minute with no heat smell and no flicker. If anything is unstable, cut power immediately.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Pass: steady light for one minute"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "troubleshoot",
                    "text": "Fail: dark, flickering, or warm components"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "troubleshoot",
            "text": "Safety stop: unplug power before touching the board. Classify the issue: (1) LED reversed, (2) resistor bypassed, or (3) loose jumper. Re-seat parts, then re-test the one-minute stability check.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "power-on-check",
                    "text": "I corrected wiring and will re-test"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify",
            "text": "Great. Record that the LED stayed lit for one minute and the resistor remained cool. Unplug the supply before any modifications so the bench remains safe for the next build.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Evidence logged and power removed"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Nice work. You completed setup, verification, and a recovery loop like a real lab run.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Thanks, Orion!"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "requiresQuests": ["welcome/howtodoquests"],
